programme.title: Welcome aboard
programme.desc: The skateboarding crew check out the cruise ship and rip around some historic streets of Italy and Greece. The first leg of the Skate Cruise sets off from Rome and travels to Savona and Mykonos. With just hours to spend at each port, the sessions are fast paced and fully improvisational. There's no time to relax when you're a skateboarding tourist.

programme.title: Turkish delights
programme.desc: With more time to explore and great spots to skate, Turkey’s Izmir and Istanbul are the trip’s best stops yet. Turkey provides the trip’s best sessions so far, with more time to explore. Izmir offers some proper transition skating at the local park, and two days in Istanbul give the crew a chance to look for bigger street spots.

programme.title: To infinity and beyond
programme.desc: The final leg sees the crew in Bulgaria and Greece. On the water, the ship’s deck is a skate spot with a view. On the last leg of the cruise, the skateboarding crew lands in Bulgaria to the warmest (albeit wettest) reception of the tour. Then it’s back to Greece, where the boys go to work on Athens’ marble with some eye-catching tricks.

programme.title: Red Bull Music Studio Sessions: Kelly Rowland
programme.desc: Kelly Rowland and producers collaborate to share an artistic journey of music writing and recording. Go behind the scenes of a creative musical journey as a team of songwriters and producers write and record three tracks with superstar singer and artist Kelly Rowland at Red Bull Studios Los Angeles.

programme.title: Frozen Mind
programme.desc: Pro snowboarder Victor De Le Rue has travelled the world, but his favourite place is Chamonix, France. Victor De Le Rue, a professional snowboarder from the Pyrenees, has ridden all over the world, but one particular place on Earth inspires him more than anywhere else: Chamonix, France.

programme.title: Against the Odds
programme.sub-title: The gaming Cinderella story - EXCLUSIVE RELEASE ON AUGUST 7TH 3PM UTC
programme.desc: This is the journey of five Dota players and a coach, who, just two months before, had never played together. In 2018 Team OG were at rock-bottom, hit by painful departures and scrapping in qualifiers for Dota 2's T18. Against the Odds is the fairytale of this broken team's shot at Gaming’s biggest prize.

programme.title: Naming pasta and track turns in Italy
programme.desc: Vanessa Guerra arrives in Italy's beautiful Tuscany and asks riders to describe the Mugello circuit. Vanessa Guerra arrives in Italy's beautiful Tuscany and asks riders to describe the Mugello circuit. Then it's time for pasta games, vlog takeovers and a ride around the track.

programme.title: The Explorers
programme.desc: Two determined innovators push their limits, risking all, in order to realise their dreams, are profiled. Pushing the limits of possibility challenges people who are willing to go beyond the visible horizon, no matter the risks. Documentary film-maker Jimmy Chin and XPRIZE creator Peter Diamandis are explorers who are always looking for a new frontier.

programme.title: The Training Heats Up
programme.desc: The b-boys train for the upoming BC One in Moscow. Lilou receives bad news and makes a strategic choice. When he discovers he can't compete in the BC One in Moscow, Lilou helps a fellow b-boy in order to beat his rival Neguin. In Sao Paulo, Neguin trains with his friend Andre. Roxrite gets an offer to compete in Moscow for the only title he's never won.

programme.title: Lessons from the Edge
programme.desc: Ultra-runners Ryan Sandes and Ryno Griesel set out to run the Great Himalaya Trail in the fastest known time. South African ultra-runners, Ryan Sandes and Ryno Griesel set out on the adventure of a lifetime: to run the Great Himalaya Trail in the fastest known time – a total of 1,406km in 28 days.

programme.title: Naming pasta and track turns in Italy
programme.desc: Vanessa Guerra arrives in Italy's beautiful Tuscany and asks riders to describe the Mugello circuit. Vanessa Guerra arrives in Italy's beautiful Tuscany and asks riders to describe the Mugello circuit. Then it's time for pasta games, vlog takeovers and a ride around the track.

programme.title: The Greasy Hands Preachers
programme.desc: Abandoning the path of a so-called normal life, a diverse group of souls prefer to build motorcycles. A diverse group of souls are united in their rejection of a traditional life. Instead, they've found their own path to enlightenment in their garages, a sense of purpose and a connection to a global family born of building and riding motorcycles.

programme.title: From the shadows
programme.desc: Unravel the mystery of the epic and forgotten wave known as Ghost Trees. By the mid-2000s, the big wave known as Ghost Trees was one of the most sought-after waves in the world, but now it’s largely unknown. Unravel the mystery of this epic and forgotten wave.

programme.title: Etnies: Album\t
programme.sub-title: Touring five continents for skate spots
programme.desc: A passionate tribe of skateboarders search cities on five continents in a quest to find new skate spots. An eclectic tribe of skateboarders scour city streets across five continents in a quest to find new skate spots. This film by Etnies is an album of moments from the years that went into the project.

programme.title: Not Bad
programme.desc: An FMB dream team chronicles a 30-day saga of mountain bike shredding and tomfoolery in New Zealand. The best riders in the game travel to New Zealand for 30 days of epic mountain bike tomfoolery. The dream team going out to go big is Brett Rheeder, Brandon Semenuk, Brook Macdonald, Cam McCaul, Andrew Shandro, Ryan Howard and René Wildhaber.

programme.title: Not2Bad
programme.desc: More epic tomfoolery in Spain. Anthill Films's sequel to Not Bad is a second dose of epic freestyle mountain biking and tomfoolery in the Spanish countryside. Featuring the talents of Brett Rheeder, Cam McCaul, Brandon Semenuk, Ryan 'R-Dog' Howard, Casey Brown and more.

programme.title: Freerunning Illusions
programme.desc: Jason Paul and Pasha Petkuns play mind tricks as they defy gravity with their freerunning illusions. Life as a freerunner means the whole world is your playground... or is it just one big illusion? Jason Paul and Pasha Petkuns play mind tricks as they defy gravity, slide down bananas, and twist your brains with their freerunning illusions.
